c distance was obtained from the <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://research.marshfieldclinic.org/genetics">Marshfield Medical Research Foundation</ext-link> web site. Marker order was established using the sequence map from the <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://genome.ucsc.edu/">UCSC Genome Bioinformatics</ext-link> site. According to this site, the order of markers is as follows: D20S199-D20S906-D20S842-D20S181-D20S193-D20S473-D20S867-D20S889-D20S116-D20S895-D20S849.</p></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap><table-wrap id="t2" position="float"><label>Table 2</label><caption><title>Primers used for the mutation analysis of the <italic>SLC4A11</italic> gene.</title></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><col width="47" span="1"/><col width="259" span="1"/><col width="74" span="1"/><col width="60" span="1"/><tbody><tr><td valign="top" align="center" scope="row" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><bold>Exon</bold><hr/></td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><bold>Sequence (5'-3')</bold><hr/></td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><bold>Annealing temperature (&#x000b0;C)</bold><hr/></td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><bold>Amplicon size (bp)</bold><hr/></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2" valign="top" align="left" scope="row" colspan="1">2<hr/></td><td valign="top" align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">F: ATTAAGGCTGGCTTCCCCTGCTATG<hr/></td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">67<hr/></td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">303<hr/></td></tr><tr><td valign="top" colspan="1" align="left" scope="col" rowspan="1">R: CCCTGGAGGCTTTTGCCCGACAAG<hr/></td><td valign="top" align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><hr/></td><td valign="top" align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><hr/></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2" valign="top" align="left" scope="row" colspan="1">3&#x00026;4<hr/></td><td valign="top" align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">F: CCTTCCTGTGTGTGGCACTTTAACAG<hr/></